DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
     The iisslloowweerr() function tests for any lower-case letter for which none of
     iscntrl(3),  isdigit(3),  ispunct(3),  or isspace(3) is true.  In the
     ``_C'' locale, iisslloowweerr() returns true only for the characters defined as
     lower-case letters.

RREETTUURRNN VVAALLUUEESS
     The iisslloowweerr() macro returns zero if the character tests false and returns
     non-zero if the character tests true.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
     isascii(3),  isalnum(3),  isalpha(3),  iscntrl(3),  isdigit(3),
     isgraph(3),  isprint(3),  ispunct(3),  isspace(3),  isupper(3),
     isxdigit(3),  toascii(3),  tolower(3),  toupper(3),  stdio(3) ascii(7)

SSTTAANNDDAARRDDSS
     The iisslloowweerr() function conforms to ANSI C3.159-1989 (``ANSI C'').

